above is the mean height of the population

pop_v <- function(h) {
    sum((h - mean(h))^2)/(length(h))
}
pop_sd <- function(h) {
    sqrt(pop_v(h))
}
pop_sd(h)
## [1] 4.30797

above is the poulation SD for height

samph <- samp$height

sampSDh
## [1] 5.30916

sampSEh
## [1] 0.9693156
upperh <- qnorm( 0.95, mean=meansh, sd=sampSDh)
upperh
## [1] 75.26246
lowerh <- qnorm( 0.05, mean=meansh, sd=sampSDh)
lowerh
## [1] 57.79688

## [1] 57.79688 75.26246
